China and Russia believe that the UN Security Council should encourage Pyongyang for the steps that have been taken.
U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told the U.N. Security Council on Thursday: “The Security Council’s imposition of sanctions should continue actively and imperatively until we see complete, final and confirmed denuclearization.”
The Security Council has unanimously tightened sanctions against North Korea since 2006, seeking to cut off funding for Pyongyang’s nuclear and ballistic missile programs.
